Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
All parameters are within normal limits except for a significantly elevated creatinine (3.2 mg/dL), indicating impaired renal function. No electrolyte disturbances or liver enzyme abnormalities are present. Lipid profile, glucose, and protein levels are unremarkable. Recommend clinical correlation for possible chronic kidney disease and further nephrological evaluation.
